'''Musanimasu Shrine''' (むさにますじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Kashihara|Q496319|qid=Q496319|1=Kashihara, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|qid=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|lt=Shikinaisha great shrine|Q134917288|qid=Q134917288|1=Shikinai Taisha}}, and its former {{ill|lt=shrine rank|Q10444029|qid=Q10444029|1=Shakaku}} was {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* '''{{ill|UNKNOWN|qid=Q125400|lt=Takamimusubi-no-Kami|1=Takamimusubi}}'''
* '''{{ill|lt=Emperor Kōgen|Q333572|qid=Q333572|1=Emperor Kōgen}}'''
As older identifications of the ancient deity, the following appear:
* {{ill|lt=Ameikutama-no-Mikoto|Q97184246|qid=Q97184246|lt=Ikudama-no-Kami|1=Ame-no-Ikutama}} (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Shoki|Q813935|qid=Q813935|1=Nihon Shoki}}'')
* Ikazuchi-no-Kami (''Gogun Jinjaki'')

=== History ===
=== Foundation ===
The origin is said to be enshrinement of Ikazuchi-no-Kami by the immigrant leader Misa no Suguri Ao in the era of {{ill|lt=Emperor Ankō|Q361010|qid=Q361010|1=Emperor Ankō}}. Misa (=Musa) was a place name in Takachi District, {{ill|lt=Yamato Province|Q907495|qid=Q907495|1=Yamato Province}}, regarded as the base area of the {{ill|lt=Yamato-no-Aya clan|Q10870550|qid=Q10870550|1=Yamatonoaya clan}} who naturalized under {{ill|lt=Achi no Omi|Q11657596|qid=Q11657596|1=Achi no Omi}}. Misa no Suguri Ao was a favored retainer of {{ill|lt=Emperor Yūryaku|Q357235|qid=Q357235|1=Emperor Yūryaku}}, one of the {{ill|lt=Five Kings of Wa|Q1152880|qid=Q1152880|1=Five kings of Wa}}. ''{{ill|lt=Nihon Shoki|Q813935|qid=Q813935|1=Nihon Shoki}}'' records missions he led to Wu/Song in Yūryaku 8 ({{ill|lt=464|Q30150|qid=Q30150|1=464}}) and Yūryaku 12 ({{ill|lt=468|Q30823|qid=Q30823|1=468}}), though these are not found in the ''{{ill|lt=Book of Song|Q1143142|qid=Q1143142|1=Book of Song}}''.

=== Historical outline ===
According to ''{{ill|lt=Nihon Shoki|Q813935|qid=Q813935|1=Nihon Shoki}}'', during the {{ill|lt=Jinshin War|Q2378252|qid=Q2378252|1=Jinshin War}}, in Takachi District, the deity “Kotoshironushi at {{ill|lt=Kawamata Shrine|Q11553360|qid=Q11553360|lt=Takachi Shrine|1=Kawamata Shrine (Q11553360)}} and Ikudama-no-Kami at Misa Shrine” possessed {{ill|lt=Takachi Agatanushi Kome|Q11669864|qid=Q11669864|lt=Takachi Agatanushi Kome|1=Takechi no Kome}} and gave an {{ill|lt=oracle|Q217123|qid=Q217123|1=Oracle}}: “Offer horses and various weapons at the tomb of {{ill|lt=Emperor Jinmu#mausoleum|Q200188|qid=Q200188|lt=Kamuyamato Iwarehiko|1=Emperor Jimmu}},” and then Prince Ōama (later {{ill|lt=Emperor Tenmu|Q335181|qid=Q335181|1=Emperor Tenmu}}) would be protected.<ref>''Nihon Shoki'', vol. 28</ref> After his enthronement, divine rank was granted to Misa-ni-masu Ikudama-no-Kami for the first time in history. In the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} it is listed as a great shrine and recorded as receiving offerings for monthly and Niiname rites.<br/>Its former rank was listed as {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Court rank ===
* {{ill|lt=Ten'an (Japan)|Q1075611|qid=Q1075611|lt=Ten'an|1=Ten'an}} 3 ({{ill|lt=859|Q23897|qid=Q23897|1=859}}), {{ill|lt=January 27|Q2284|qid=Q2284|1=January 27}}: promoted from Junior Fifth Lower to Junior Fifth Upper (''{{ill|lt=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku|Q1052981|qid=Q1052981|1=Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku}}'') - written as “Musanimasu-no-Kami.”

=== Access ===
* Just west on foot from {{ill|lt=Okadera Station|Q7081721|qid=Q7081721|1=Okadera Station}} on the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Yoshino Line|1=UNKNOWN}} of {{ill|lt=Kintetsu|Q1531085|qid=Q1531085|1=Kintetsu Railway}}.

